  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is aimed to assess a new system for the automatic detection, quantification and
      treatment of Near Fall (NF) episodes in healthy older adults with a history of falls. The
      system is comprized of a treadmill and a virtual reality simulation which provides a
      motor-cognitive challenge to provoke NF. The challenges provided by the system are
      individualized and using machine learning algorithms will enable the identification and
      detection of NF under different conditions and allow for the most suitable treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
